#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pre-requisites
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"pyFoam testing" an automatic non-regression test environment requires the following
products to be run.

* Make sure that confFoam (common configuration package) is installed 
  Can be found at https://vulashaka.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/vulashaka/conffoam.
  Please follow instructions from corresponding INSTALL file to setup confFoam
  in your environment.

* Install pyFoam
  Can be found at https://vulashaka.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/vulashaka/pyfoam.
  Please follow instructions from corresponding INSTALL file to setup pyfoam
  in your environment.

Then follow the instructions below in order to prepare the "pyFoam-testing" environment 
to be run.


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Basic Installation
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The configure procedure of the "pyFoam-testing" package is based on GNU autoconf utility. 
In order to prepare the environment you have to perform the following actions:

1. Start a new shell session (to ensure a clear environment).

2. Go to the source directory:

   cd <path to the sources>

3. Modify the provided "env.sh" file to adjust to your local environment.
   
   <your favorite editor> ./env.sh

4. Source this "env.sh" file to define the corresponding build environment.

   source ./env.sh

5. Configuring the build system:

   build_configure
   ./configure

   Make sure that after each configuration step the "--- OK ---" message is
   printed in your console.


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"pyFoam-testing" environment
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Before start to use "pyFoam-testing" it is necessary to source the generated "bashrc" file


#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
"pyFoam-testing" check
#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Run all the provided "pyFoam-testing" cases, for example

  ${PYFOAM_TESTING_DIR}/cases/run

Clean the results of the previous "pyFoam-testing" runs

  ${PYFOAM_TESTING_DIR}/cases/clean


